npm install -g @cypress/cli
```

### Step-by-Step Guide

#### 1. Setting Up Cypress

First, initialize a Cypress project:

```sh
npx @cypress/cli init my-cypress-app
cd my-cypress-app
npm install --global @cypress/cypress-cli
```

#### 2. Creating a Dockerfile

Create a Dockerfile to set up the Docker environment for Cypress.

```dockerfile
# Use an official Node.js image as a parent image
FROM node:14

# Set the working directory in the container
WORKDIR /app

# Copy the package.json and package-lock.json files into the container
COPY package*.json./

# Install Cypress and other dependencies
RUN npm install

# Copy the rest of the application code into the container
COPY..

# Expose the port Cypress uses to communicate with the host
EXPOSE 3000

# Command to run Cypress on the host
CMD ["cypress", "--target", "html5", "--debug", "--allow-root"]
```

#### 3. Building Docker Images

Build the Docker images for Cypress:

```sh
docker build -t my-cypress-app.
```

#### 4. Running Cypress in Docker

Run Cypress in the Docker container:

```sh
docker run -p 3000:3000 my-cypress-app
```

#### 5. Setting Up Cypress to Capture Screenshots

